You can store a count in Inline editor. There are two options for storing data and you can choose based on whether you want to save data within a conversation or across conversations. If it is within conversation (your game score for current session) use `conversationToken`. Example:

    let conv = agent.conv(); // create an instance
    conv.data.pointspt1 = 0;
    conv.data.pointsp2 = 1;
    const total = conv.data.pointspt1 + conv.data.pointspt2;
    agent.add(`Your total score is ${total}`);
    // If you want to save data across conversations
    conv.user.storage.pointspt1 = 0; // This works only for verified users

Refer to the following link for more informations: [Save data in conversation][1]


  [1]: https://developers.google.com/assistant/conversational/save-data

